TITLE: Kansas City becomes latest Dem-run city to form reparations commission, seek payments for Black residents
SUMMARY: Kansas City's reparations commission is up and running with the appointment of 13 members who will be seeking taxpayer dollars for payments to eligible Black residents in the area.

TITLE: Critics explode over US Navy's use of drag queen to solve recruiting crisis: 'What NOT to do'
SUMMARY: Critics exploded on the U.S. Navy over its decision to use a drag queen sailor to help persuade new recruits amid the military's massive recruitment crisis.

TITLE: California leads blue state charge against Florida restrictions on transition surgeries
SUMMARY: California Attorney General Rob Bonta is leading a charge of Democratic-led states against Florida's new rule banning Medicaid dollars from being used for transition surgeries.

TITLE: Billionaire Dem mega-donor bankrolling Trump accuser's rape lawsuit visited Epstein's private island
SUMMARY: A billionaire Democratic mega-donor who's currently bankrolling a rape lawsuit against former President Donald Trump visited the private island of sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.

TITLE: NJ Republicans eye wind turbine construction moratorium over whale death concerns
SUMMARY: New Jersey Republicans and other opponents of shoreside wind turbines have proposed a moratorium of up to 60 days on construction to assess potential effects on whale mortality.

TITLE: Illinois school backtracks after segregating math classes for Black, 'Latinx' students
SUMMARY: An Illinois high school has reversed course after it appeared to restrict access to certain Advanced Placement Calculus courses to Black and Latinx students only.

TITLE: Vermont Legislature urged to impeach prosecutor over harassment, discrimination claims
SUMMARY: The Vermont Legislature has been advised to impeach Franklin County State's Attorney John Lavoie after harassment and discrimination claims against him were determined to have merit.

TITLE: Ted Cruz says Biden's 'mental faculties are too diminished' for debt ceiling talks
SUMMARY: More than a dozen Senate Republicans stood shoulder to shoulder on Wednesday in a show of unity behind the House GOP's debt limit bill.

TITLE: Biden nominee pushing electric vehicles faces massive opposition from energy industry
SUMMARY: A sizable coalition of some of the nation's leading oil and gas industry organizations is sounding the alarm on President Biden's pick to lead an obscure agency.

TITLE: Sen. Rand Paul takes aim at Dr. Fauci in new book focused on the COVID-19 'cover-up'
SUMMARY: Sen. Rand Paul will release a book in October focusing on the origins of the coronavirus, as well as Dr. Anthony Fauci's role in the pandemic.

TITLE: Wisconsin lawmakers introduce healthcare cost transparency bill
SUMMARY: A proposal by Republicans in the Wisconsin Legislature would impose daily fines ranging from $600 to $10,000 on hospitals that fail to comply with federal cost transparency regulations.

TITLE: DeSantis backs bill to let 18-year-olds buy rifles
SUMMARY: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis on Wednesday backed a bill that would lower the minimum age to purchase a rifle to 18 in his state, calling current law "unconstitutional."

TITLE: Federal prosecutors near decision on Hunter Biden probe: report
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors investigating President Biden's son Hunter Biden for alleged gun- and tax-related violations are reportedly nearing a decision in the four-year probe.

TITLE: Biden proposes tighter national security rules around military bases after Chinese real estate purchases
SUMMARY: The Biden administration is proposing to tighten security around eight new military installations by requiring a close review of nearby property transactions.

TITLE: Florida bill clears $12M for DeSantis' migrant relocation initiative months after Martha's Vineyard flights
SUMMARY: The Florida GOP controlled legislature passed sweeping immigration bill that allocates $12 million to Gov. Ron DeSantis' "Unauthorized Alien Transport Program."

TITLE: Companies authorized to dodge excessive federal regulations under GOP bill
SUMMARY: Sen. Joni Ernst spoke with reporters in her office just before unveiling the Prove It Act of 2023 to coincide with Small Business Week.

TITLE: California Democrat in key House race reveals DUI charges: 'I am so deeply sorry'
SUMMARY: California state Senator David Min made a Facebook post revealing and apologizing for a misdemeanor citation for driving under the influence.

TITLE: Native American tribe condemns Biden admin effort to ban oil, gas leasing on lands
SUMMARY: The Navajo Nation's legislative council approved a resolution this week condemning and opposing a Biden administration proposal banning oil and gas drilling.

TITLE: Texas bill would let state secretary redo county election during ballot shortage
SUMMARY: The Texas state senate has passed a bill that would grant the state secretary authority to order elections be redone if ballot shortages compromise voting.

TITLE: New York Republican Lee Zeldin 'keeping an eye' on run against Democrat Sen Kirsten Gillibrand
SUMMARY: Former GOP Rep. Lee Zeldin, who ran against New York Gov. Kathy Hochul, said he would "keep on eye on" Democrat Sen. Kirsten Gillibrand's reelection bid.

TITLE: Oregon Democrats backpedal after massive public outcry against bill allowing homeless to sue over encampments
SUMMARY: Oregon lawmakers were scheduled to hold a public hearing this week on a bill decriminalizing homeless camping. Then thousands of negative comments poured in.

TITLE: Whistleblower alleges FBI, DOJ have document revealing criminal scheme involving Biden, foreign national
SUMMARY: A whistleblower is alleging that the FBI and the Justice Department are in possession of a document that describes an alleged criminal scheme involving then-Vice President Joe Biden and a foreign national relating to the exchange of money for policy decisions, House Oversight Committee Chairman James Comer and Sen. Chuck Grassley said Wednesday.

TITLE: Nearly half of all 2022 midterm voters cast ballots early or by mail
SUMMARY: According to new data released by the U.S. Census Bureau, casting ballots early or by mail were popular voting methods during the 2022 midterm elections.

TITLE: Innocent LA father killed after DA Gascon gives violent career criminal multiple diversions
SUMMARY: A career criminal who Los Angeles District Attorney George Gascon's office kept out of jail is accused of killing a father of two in April, police say.

TITLE: Trump, Haley, DeSantis? Here's everyone running, rumored, or sitting out the GOP 2024 presidential primary
SUMMARY: Here’s a look at who’s in – Trump, Haley, others - and who may be getting in -DeSantis, Pence, Scott, and others - in the race for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination.
